==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trudgen stroke
<hw>Trudg"en stroke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Swimming)</fld> <def>A
racing stroke in which a double over-arm motion is used; -- so called
from its use by an amateur named <person>Trudgen</person>, but often
erroneously written <asp>trudgeon</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>True</ent>⟦br⟧
